===Etymology===
From {{F.}} ''[[crier]]'', compare Latin ''[[quiritare]]'' "to raise a plaintive cry", "[[scream]]", "[[shriek]]", perhaps {{F.}} ''[[queri]]'' "to complain"; compare Sanskrit ''cvas'' "to [[pant]]", "[[hiss]]", "[[sigh]]". Compare [[quarrel]] a brawl, [[querulous]].

===Intransitive verb===
{{en-verb|cr|i|ed}}

# To [[shed]] [[tears]]; to [[weep]].
#:''That sad movie always makes me '''cry'''.''
# To [[shout]], [[scream]], [[yell]].
#:''The captured bear cub tried to '''cry''' out to its mother.''

